AGI - The resumption of the Israeli military offensive in Gaza > caused the death of at least 322 children in ten days, in the Palestinian territory already hard hit by the siege. It was announced by Unnicef>. "It is believed that the breakup of ceasefire and the resumption of intense bombing and land operations in the Gaza Strip caused the death of at least 322 children > and the wounding of another 609, which represents a daily average of over 100 children killed or mutilated in the last ten days," said the agency Onu for childhood in a statement.
According to UNICEF, "the majority of these children were displaced and took refuge in tents of luck or in damaged houses", a situation that reflects the precariousness of living conditions almost two weeks after Israel's resumption of military operations. The organization pointed out that estimates also include children who may have been killed or injured during the March 23rd attack at the Nasser> Hospital surgery department in the south of the Strip.
<div </div
Israel relaunched its military campaign on 18 March, with intense bombings and a new offensive of land, interrupting the truce with Hamas which had entered into force on 19 January. "The ceasefire provided a desperately necessary security network for Gaza children," said Catherine Russell, Director of UNICEF. Now, "the children are again immersed in a cycle of mortal violence and deprivation," he added.
From the resumption of the offensive, according to the Ministry of Health of Hamas, 1,001 people were killed in Gaza, bringing the total budget of the victims to 50,357 dead from the beginning of the war, burst after the attack of the Islamist movement against Israel on 7 October 2023. According to UNICEF there are 15,000 children.&nbsp;
